title: Full Stack Developer
description: Collaborated with a team of nine developers to create an event organization and student management application for the London Boys and Girls Club. I utilized React and Figma to design and build components and then GitHub to connect the frontend with Firebase and develop a full stack application.

title: Vice President Social
description: Organized weekly social events such as section dinners, golf, and bar nights for my 80-person cohort by connecting with local businesses to arrange reservations and build relationships for the program. The highlight trips were Niagara Falls and Blue Mountains, check out the pictures!

title: Debate Competitor
description: Competed in a two-person team debate competition hosted by Western Engineering. In my first debate competition I advanced to the finals, placed second overall and received an invitation to the Provincial Debate Championships.

title: Engineering Leader
description: Mentored 23 first year engineering students throughout the year by endorsing university resources and providing social support, ensuring students were accustomed to university and positioned for success.

title: Researcher
description: Activity participated in weekly educational meeting lead by the Tech, Media and Telecom group which has solidified my interest in investing. Has a researcher I wrote a one-page stock analysis on Intel (NASDAQ: INTC) as a part of an exclusive Equity Monitoring team.

title: Oshawa Division Co-Led
description: Led an expansion division of a non-profit organization that created and distributed Covid-19 relief baskets to the homeless; resulted in 125 relief baskets being delivered to the Oshawa homeless community.

title: Innertube Water Polo Player
description: Played two games of innertube water polo each Saturday night at the Western Recreational Centre. Unfournatly our season was cut short due to COVID-19, although my team is excited to play again when it is safe to do so.

title: Western Ambassador
description: Attended weekly “mix night” sessions run by the team, where we would make the concrete for the skis of the toboggan. In our National Competition, we placed third overall at the competition, after winning first in Ski Design, first in Theme, third in Spirit, and third in Toboggan Design.
